Installation
------------
1. Install node.js (on Debian/Ubuntu: "apt-get install nodejs"). We recommend to use node version manager (https://github.com/creationix/nvm)
We use js generators, so you have to use node version >= 0.11 (nvm install 0.12.7)
2. Run "npm i" in project root to install dependencies. ("sudo npm i" can be required, depending on node.js installation)
3. Install postgres and pgAdmin on your machine
4. Create database and restore it from last backup (/db_dump/indaba{mmdd}.backup), using pgAdmin restore–≤
5. Configure application (rename config_etalon.js to config.js)
6. Run application "node --harmony app.js". We use generators, so you need to use "--harmony" flag.

